# Load Ledgers V5 — security response headers for Cloudflare Pages.
#
# BEARDS DOCTRINE — Truth as Architecture: security is enforced at the edge on
# every response, not left to chance. These headers are what the Mozilla HTTP
# Observatory grades. Applied to every path on the site.
#
# WHAT EACH HEADER DOES (and which Observatory test it fixes):
#   Strict-Transport-Security : forces HTTPS for 2 years, eligible for preload.   (HSTS test)
#   Content-Security-Policy   : whitelists exactly what the app may load/connect. (CSP test)
#   X-Frame-Options + frame-ancestors 'none' : blocks clickjacking / embedding.   (X-Frame-Options test)
#   X-Content-Type-Options    : already passing; kept here so it never regresses.
#   Referrer-Policy           : already passing; kept explicit.
#   Permissions-Policy        : disables APIs the app never uses (camera mic etc).
#
# CSP NOTE: the allow-list below is built for what loadledgers ACTUALLY uses —
# its own origin, Google Fonts, and the ledger-v5 Worker API. If a future
# feature loads from a new origin, that origin must be added here or it will be
# blocked. 'unsafe-inline' is included for style/script because the app and the
# static pages use inline styles and small inline scripts; removing it later
# (via hashes/nonces) would raise the grade further but is not required for A.

/*
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=63072000; includeSubDomains; preload
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://fonts.googleapis.com; font-src 'self' https://fonts.gstatic.com; img-src 'self' data: blob: https://ledger-v5.d49rwgmpj9.workers.dev; connect-src 'self' https://ledger-v5.d49rwgmpj9.workers.dev; frame-ancestors 'none'; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'self'; object-src 'none'
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: geolocation=(), microphone=(), camera=(), payment=()
